rComments: the content is very heavy but if you ask him for help on assignments or content he goes above and beyond. Always gives hints during lecture on what he will test on. He wants everyone to do well and really cares about the students. i'm not a A+ student but if you put can put in the work I really recommend this course to anyone considering it!

He is an amazing prof! He's really really caring and literally cuts down any work you have to do by providing you with lecture notes. Literally just learn his lecture notes and u'll be gold. I will say many of his questions on the exams made you think, so know everything WELL!

Great prof, he makes detailed notes alongside lecture slides which are more than enough for what you need on the exam  which was fairly straightforward by the way. Thought he was a bit awkward at first but honestly hes a great lecturer and you will do great in his module as long as you put in the effort.

He really cares about his students learning, I even saw him make notes for himself so he can improve for next year. Its very detailed but he explains very well and he even gives you notes to study off of. He also gives you practice questions that are similar to ones you would see in the exam. But make sure you actually read his notes at least.
teacherRatingTags: ['Amazing lectures', 'Lecture heavy', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: His lectures are all so clear. Everything is extremely well explained. He provides notes to replace the textbook and they cover EVERYTHING you need to know for the exam. If you read the notes carefully and attend lectures, you will know the material like the back of your hand and be more than prepared for the exam. Best prof Ive had!
teacherRatingTags: ['Amazing lectures', 'Get ready to read', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: Overall an excellent professor. Provides his own notes that replace the textbook. Everything you need to succeed in the course is literally handed to you. Although notes can be heavy and he can be a bit nit picky on detail, it's all on the paper so as long you understand it rather than merely memorize it you are good to go.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Test heavy', 'Clear grading criteria']

rComments: Lab portion is very easy, get all the marks you can from this portion of the course. Exams are very difficult if you don't know the material inside and out.

This is core physiology stuff and he makes sure students get the brunt of it. Has hundreds of pages of notes to memorize for a cumulative final (which he says can replace a bad midterm - never happens). Labs were the only good part only to realize the reports had abstract, unclear questions graded at TA's discretion. Study hard for both exams.

His exam q's are "fair" but the final is cumulative so the questions don't seem so fair when u have to memorize 200+ pages of detailed notes. Labs were fun and a great experience. Lab report q's were tough, but doable. Study the ENTIRE lab manual for the lab exam and pls don't count on the final to replace your midterm mark. You'll thank me later.
teacherRatingTags: ["Skip class? You won't pass.", 'Tough grader', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: This prof. is extremely fair. As long as you either add  lecture notes to his power point slides or add your own notes based on the additional notes he provides to the slides you can do EXTREMELY well on the exam. The exam was fair and his sample questions were very helpful so it is definitely possible to get a high grade.
cool dude

As a first year student, he was the most fair prof I've had. His lectures were somewhat heavy but very detailed, his exam was easy. He focused on general info and was not very picky on detail. Make sure to look over his review ppt/word doc before the exam as it covers all the important info needed to focus on. Hope I get him in upper year classes!
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Lecture heavy', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: as long as you memorize his notes he gives, you'll be fine a loooot of content, but he gives you everything you need to know  exam was semi-tough but he literally gives you all the info you need to memorize. start studying at least a week before bc theres a lot of info in his notes

Phenomenal lecture slides, content is clear, concise, and informative. You shouldn't see a question on the exam that wasn't covered via lecture (provided you're actually reading the lectures). Although he doesn't provide readings for the textbook he discloses that the content on the exam is solely from lecture content, fantastic professor.
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Amazing lectures', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Lectures are awful. Cannot stand to sit through them in one sitting. His voice is very monotone. He doesn't really seem to have a passion in what he is teaching (maybe that's just his monotone, dreadful voice).

Professor Reid is a great prof. His lectures are very clear and he provides you with very detailed notes so you can easily understand everything he teaches. His exams are quite difficult, but I thought that was only fair because he teaches so well. He marks fairly. If you study hard, you should be fine.

His lectures were quite dry and monotone. He threw a load of information at the class in one sitting. Although he is a very knowledgable and well-spoken professor, I did not feel engaged at all during his lectures.
Really clear and well spoken prof. Nice guy too BUT his courses are not as EASY as people are saying, he marks ok but not a 4.0 prof
Very organized prof. Tough exams but very fair grading. Class was interesting.

Dr. Reid's notes were amazing and was very helpful in getting a good grade on the exam. You don't need to read the textbook as everything you need to know is on the slides and notes. The  exam review lecture was very helpful and everyone was able to get a good grade with him
He makes everything so clear! Extremely organized and fair. THE best course I've ever taken at UTSC.

Professor Reid is the most organized professor on this campus. You do *NOT* need the textbook, as his notes (handouts, not slides) are amazing and everything you need to know for the exams. There's a lot of material though, so study hard. The labs aren't stressful at all - boost your grade with it and the reports afterwards!

My favourite prof! If you put in the work and keep up to date with the material it's pretty straight forward. You do need to know the material inside out. Don't expect to do better on the final than the midterm! You will most likely get roughly the same grade. If your a 4.0 student his class won't bring down your average, if not watch out!

This course is interesting. You need to go to class to understand the material on the slides. He talks fast so the weboption helped. There is 2 midterms and a final. MC as well as 5-8 long answers. He gives you hint what long answers are. Class average was B-. He questions are a bit hard and short answers they are picky. MC for the final was harder

He is an excellent professor. Yes, boring at times but does an amazing job of thoroughly explaining all the content detail by detal which is exactly what you need to ace the course. His lecture notes are amazing! Exams are fair if you study and review a lot.

Great course if you are interested in physiology or a career in medical sciences. His explains everything clearly, albeit the course is dense. Lab exam is harder than expected, don't underestimate it (lower class avg than midterm). Do his practice questions in his study guides and look over his lecture notes thoroughly. Not an easy course but fair.

He is such a great and knowledgeable prof, like he really knows what he's doing. His lectures have so much detail, and you don't even need a textbook. His exams are hard, but rewatching his lectures and understanding his slides will really help.

When comparing all the profs in my 1st year, this prof would be the best. At first, I hated his lectures because they were so long and boring. But when I studied for the exam, they were so helpful. Did not need to open the textbook once. His slides are detailed and he explains slowly and clearly. Hope I get him again for another class!
He was able to explain dozens of pages in the textbook and place it all in one lecture slide. I love his sens of humour and how he puts funny images to keep the course interesting

A great professor indeed. I always watch his lectures online and i have to say he is soo good at delivering the material and keeping it as interesting as possible. His lectures explained everything way better than the book and to the point. Hope to have him again for future biology courses. His exam was... HARD!

He is an extremely knowledgeable prof, and has a lot to offer if you're willing to put in the work. I watched his lectures online, memorized his lectures so well that I could repeat them word for word in my sleep, and I got an 'A' in the course. Midterm and final are difficult. Make sure you dedicate a lot of time studying the notes. Great course!

Lots of material for this course, you should probably love biology if youre taking this otherwise it will be a drag. He is quite monotonous,the lectures are not fascinating. He tests very fairly, provides lots of practice questions. Lab exam was not easy. Midterm and final are fair (midtrm avg 74%) give yourself time to study and you will ace!

Extremely knowledgeable prof...really knows his stuff and it shows in lectures. The course is really dense, but you learn a lot. Make sure to do well on the midterm because the final is lengthy and difficult.

Midterm was really easy, so much so that one section had an average of 80%. Final was extremely difficult, average was 53%. Beware of his T.A. Jessica, pray she never marks your labs. She is rude, and not helpful. He is a good Prof, but after the final a lot of people hate him. I dropped by about 15%. BEWARE OF THE FINAL!!!!!!!!!!!!
Midterm and lab assignments were easy. Good lecturer. An all-around nice prof.....until he KILLS you on the FINAL!!! class average was 53%! your mark can drop by 10% easily!

His midterm and assignments are pretty simple and clear. There's no need for the textbook if you watch the online lectures. The FINAL was intense. 100 questions in 3 hours is pretty average....but rarely does 100 questions take up 31 pages. Very detailed. my brain was cramping by question 50. BRUTAL.

One of the best profs at UTSC. He knows his stuff and explains some of the most complex stuff about physiology really really well. The notes he gives are really clear. I'm looking foward to taking BGYD33 with him next year!
What an awesome Prof!!  Physiology is suddenly cool!  Also, what a hottie, though I wish he still wore his tight shirts.
Interesting course.
What an amazing professor!!. His lectures are always clear, and interesting. He obviously spends hours and hours and home preparing them way in advance, right Prof. Reid ;).
Fair i guess, more enthusiasm would be good
Overall, I think he is a good prof....and kind of cute looking.  This is a good course and I strongly recommend it.
Excellent teching skills. Well presented lectures. Made the material in the text book easy to understand.
Very good! - Works hard to make the information clear and interesting. A+++
A really good professor and he does a great job in making the course material clear, and interesting.

I am sad to say that i was bored out of my minddddddddddddd! His voice was too monotonous, i felt that you simply read out of your overheads which i could have done at home myself. Sorry, i know you tried....
You perform well as a university prof.
Really interesting, and a really fair examiner
Very clear and understandable lectures.
